    <title>Refugees contributor: Claas Schneiderheinze</title>
    <description>Claas Schneiderheinze is a researcher at the Kiel Institute for the World Economy. He completed a bachelor of economics in Kiel and a master of development economics in Göttingen. In September of 2016 he joined the Kiel Institute’s department of poverty reduction, equity and development as a research fellow and PhD candidate. He is funded by the MEDAM project and mainly works on the country of origin perspective.
